title: Manitowoc Lincoln boys 3rd at Wisconsin Rapids Invite
text:
Manitowoc Lincoln boys 3rd at Wisconsin Rapids Invite HTR Media 9:01 p.m. CDT October 10, 2015 CROSS COUNTRY 24 CONNECT 2 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Despite not having a runner finish higher than 17th, the Manitowoc Lincoln boys cross country finished third at the Wisconsin Rapids Invite. 
Drew Hoffman was 17th to lead the Ships, which had all five scoring runners finish within 30 seconds of each other. 
The girls took eighth as a team, propelled by Macie Brogan’s third-place finish. 
Boys 
Team scores: Stevens Point 40, Darlington 92, Manitowoc Lincoln 118, Rosholt 136, Wisconsin Rapids 183, Assumption 189, Sparta 194, Mauston 202, Oshkosh West 219, Onalaska Luther 263, Oshkosh Lourdes 302, Marshfield 310, Sauk Prairie 324, Waukesha South 346, Tomah 350, Adams-Friendship 493, Clintonville 506
